  "text": "## CRD Validation to OpenAPI Schema Publishing Chain\n\n### Overview\nThe Kubernetes API server implements a multi-stage pipeline to convert CustomResourceDefinition (CRD) validation schemas into OpenAPI specifications that are published via HTTP endpoints.\n\n### Stage 1: CRD Validation Schema Definition\n\nThe validation schema for a CRD is defined through the `JSONSchemaProps` type in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/v1/types_jsonschema.go`. This structure implements JSON Schema Draft 4 and includes properties for:\n- Basic type information (type, format, description)\n- Value constraints (minimum, maximum, pattern, enum)\n- Structural properties (properties, additionalProperties, items)\n- Kubernetes-specific extensions (x-kubernetes-preserve-unknown-fields, x-kubernetes-int-or-string, x-kubernetes-list-type, etc.)\n- Validation rules (x-kubernetes-validations)\n\nThe CRD resource itself is defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/v1/types.go` and includes a reference to `CustomResourceDefinitionVersion`, which contains the `OpenAPIV3Schema` field that holds the JSONSchemaProps.\n\n### Stage 2: Structural Schema Extraction\n\nThe structural schema is an intermediate representation that extracts only the schema information relevant to object structure. The `NewStructural` function in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/convert.go` converts the `JSONSchemaProps` into a `Structural` schema.\n\nThe `Structural` type in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/structural.go` is composed of:\n- `Generic`: Type, description, title, default, nullable\n- `Extensions`: Kubernetes vendor extensions\n- `ValidationExtensions`: CEL validation rules\n- `ValueValidation`: Constraints on values\n\nEach structural schema recursively references nested structural schemas for properties, items, and additionalProperties. This filtering removes unsupported schema features and validates the schema structure for use as an object definition.\n\n### Stage 3: OpenAPI v3 Schema Conversion\n\nThe `ToKubeOpenAPI()` method in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/kubeopenapi.go` converts a structural schema into an OpenAPI spec.Schema object (from k8s.io/kube-openapi). This conversion:\n- Recursively processes nested properties\n- Maps structural type information to OpenAPI format\n- Preserves Kubernetes-specific vendor extensions\n- Converts validation constraints to OpenAPI equivalents\n\nThe `BuildOpenAPIV3` function in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/builder.go` orchestrates the full conversion pipeline:\n1. Calls `generateBuilder` which extracts the CRD schema and creates a structural schema\n2. Calls `schema.ToKubeOpenAPI()` to convert to OpenAPI format\n3. Uses kube-openapi's builder3 to generate the complete OpenAPI v3 specification including paths, operations, and schemas\n\nFor OpenAPI v2, the `BuildOpenAPIV2` function performs a similar process.\n\n### Stage 4: OpenAPI Spec Merging\n\nThe `MergeSpecsV3` function in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/merge.go` merges OpenAPI specifications from multiple CRDs into a single specification by combining their schema definitions and API paths. It handles conflicts by prioritizing built-in Kubernetes types (io.k8s.apimachinery, io.k8s.api.autoscaling) and preventing CRD-defined types from overriding them.\n\n### Stage 5: API Server Spec Endpoint Publication\n\nThe `Controller` in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapiv3/controller.go` implements the main publishing mechanism:\n- Watches CustomResourceDefinition objects for additions, updates, and deletions\n- For each CRD version, calls `buildV3Spec` which invokes `builder.BuildOpenAPIV3`\n- Stores the generated spec in an internal map indexed by group version\n- Calls `updateGroupVersion` which merges all specs for a group version\n- Publishes the merged spec to the `OpenAPIV3Service` via `UpdateGroupVersion`\n\nSimilarly, the `Controller` in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/controller.go` handles OpenAPI v2 publishing.\n\nThe OpenAPI controllers are registered as post-start hooks in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/apiserver.go` at line 238:\n```go\nif s.GenericAPIServer.OpenAPIV3VersionedService != nil {\n    openapiv3Controller := openapiv3controller.NewController(s.Informers.Apiextensions().V1().CustomResourceDefinitions())\n    go openapiv3Controller.Run(s.GenericAPIServer.OpenAPIV3VersionedService, hookContext.Done())\n}\n```\n\nThe `OpenAPIV3Service` (from k8s.io/kube-openapi) handles serving the OpenAPI v3 specification at the `/openapi/v3` endpoint, and similarly for OpenAPI v2 at `/openapi/v2`.\n\n### Complete Data Flow\n\nCRD YAML → CustomResourceDefinition object → JSONSchemaProps → NewStructural → Structural schema → ToKubeOpenAPI → OpenAPI spec.Schema → BuildOpenAPIV3 → Full OpenAPI v3 spec → MergeSpecsV3 (with other CRD specs) → OpenAPIV3Service → HTTP /openapi/v3 endpoint"
